Information was received on 28-Dec-2014.   This is a spontaneous, published case reported by a physician 
referring to a 60 year-old female patient who experienced progressive multifocal leukoencephalopathy during 
Prograf (tacrolimus) treatment. 
Citations Included
 - Carlson N, Hansen JM Fatal Progressive Multifocal Leukoencephalopathy in a Kidney Transplant Recipient 19 
Years After Successful Renal Allograft Transplantation. Transplantation Proceedings. 2014; vol. 46; pp. 2403-5. 
Other suspect medications included mycophenolic acid.
